gdrive_guide_text="
1. ACCESS THE GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE:
   → Go to console.cloud.google.com and log in with your Google account

2. CREATE A NEW PROJECT:
   → In the top left, click the project dropdown and select \"New Project\"
   → Name it (e.g., \"RcloneDrive\") and click \"Create\"
   → Wait and ensure it is selected

3. ENABLE THE GOOGLE DRIVE API:
   → In the left sidebar, go to \"APIs & Services\" > \"Library\"
   → Search for \"Google Drive API\" and click it
   → Click the blue \"Enable\" button

4. CONFIGURE THE OAUTH CONSENT SCREEN:
   → In the left menu, go to \"APIs & Services\" > \"OAuth consent screen\"
   → Choose User Type: \"External\" (for @gmail.com) or \"Internal\" (for Workspace)
   → Fill in required fields:
     • App name: \"RcloneApp\" (or your preference)
     • User support email: Your email
     • Developer contact: Your email
   → Click \"Save and Continue\" (skip Scopes screen, just click again)
   → On \"Test users\" screen: Click \"+ Add Users\" and add your Google Drive email
   → Click \"Save and Continue\"

5. CREATE CREDENTIALS:
   → In the left menu, click \"Credentials\"
   → Click \"+ Create Credentials\" and select \"OAuth client ID\"
   → Select \"Desktop app\" as Application type
   → Give it a name and click \"Create\"

6. SAVE THE KEYS:
   → A window will show your \"Client ID\" and \"Client Secret\"
   → Have these ready for the next step!

Once you've completed these steps, click OK to continue."

odrive_guide_text="
INSTRUCTIONS FOR ONEDRIVE PERSONAL

1. Register an App Name for CLIENT ID
   → Open https://portal.azure.com/?quickstart=true#view/Microsoft_AAD_IAM/ActiveDirectoryMenuBlade/~/Overview and then under the Add menu click App registration.
      • If you have not created an Azure account, you will be prompted to. This is free, but you need to provide a phone number, address, and credit card for identity verification.

   → Enter a name for your 'app', choose account type Accounts in any organizational directory (Any Azure AD directory - Multitenant) and personal Microsoft accounts (e.g. Skype, Xbox)
   → Select Web in Redirect URI, then type (do not copy and paste) http://localhost:53682/ and click Register. Copy and keep the Application (client) ID under the app name.

2. Get the account SECRET
   → Under manage select Certificates & secrets, click New client secret. Enter a description (can be anything) and set Expires to 24 months. 
   → Copy and keep that secret Value (you won't be able to see this value afterwards).

3. Final preparations
   → Under manage select API permissions, click Add a permission and select Microsoft Graph then select delegated permissions.
   → Search and select the following permissions: Files.Read, Files.ReadWrite, Files.Read.All, Files.ReadWrite.All, offline_access, User.Read and Sites.Read.All. Once selected click Add permissions at the bottom.

Once you've completed these steps, click OK to continue."

